<li class="comment byuser comment-author-hamisun odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="li-comment-350714">
<article id="comment-350714" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/Hael-from-the-manhwa-Id.jpg" width="50" height="44" alt="hamisun" class="avatar avatar-50 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo"/><span class="fn"><b>hamisun</b> <br/><br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-3-chapter-2-2/#comment-350714"><time datetime="2016-05-16T16:29:58+00:00"> May 16, 2016 at 4:29 pm</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>hiding the ring in his mouth&#8230; I loled.<br/>
Really, if they even took his buttons, then they would definitely have searched his mouth. I mean, they think he&#8217;s a foreign spy. Fake teeth and cyanide pills, anyone? They would definitely have found the ring in an actual situation like this.<br/>
Plot hole.<br/>
But still, don&#8217;t get me wrong, it&#8217;s a great story ^_^</p>
</div> 
<div class="reply">
<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="https://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wuxiaworld.com%2Fti-index%2Fti-vol-3-chapter-2-2%2F">Log in to Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div> 
</article> 
<ol class="children">
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-piledriver even depth-2" id="li-comment-354739">
<article id="comment-354739" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/bHK4Cep.jpg" width="50" height="50" alt="piledriver" class="avatar avatar-50 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo"/><span class="fn"><b>piledriver</b> <br/><br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-3-chapter-2-2/#comment-354739"><time datetime="2016-05-20T14:29:59+00:00"> May 20, 2016 at 2:29 pm</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>It could be bad writing, a misinformation, lack of prior information, plot armor or the police/army/special agents are just dumb. But certainly it&#8217;s NOT a plot hole. A Plot Hole rarely appears, if ever, in any literature.</p>
<p>The most clear-cut way to identify a Plot Hole is that first and foremost, it must be a &#8220;Contradiction or Inconsistency&#8221; of prior,stated facts or events to recently laid out facts or events.</p>
</div> 
<div class="reply">
<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="https://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wuxiaworld.com%2Fti-index%2Fti-vol-3-chapter-2-2%2F">Log in to Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div> 
</article> 
</li> 
